<h2>1. Your Website Has No SEO Strategy</h2>

<p>
Many websites fail because they don’t target the right keywords.
</p>

<p>
Instead of targeting high-intent searches like:
</p>

<ul>
<li>“best SEO services in Nairobi”</li>
<li>“affordable digital marketing agency in Kenya”</li>
<li>“Shopify SEO expert in Nairobi Kenya”</li>
</ul>

<p>
They use generic or irrelevant keywords.
</p>

<p>
👉 Fix: Use a clear SEO strategy with long-tail keywords.  
Learn how here:  
<a href="/blog/best-seo-services-nairobi-2026.html" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">
Best SEO Services in Nairobi Guide
</a>
</p>

---

<h2>2. Your Website Is Not Indexed by Google</h2>

<p>
If Google hasn’t indexed your site, it simply won’t appear in search results.
</p>

<p>
👉 Fix:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Submit your site in Google Search Console</li>
<li>Request indexing for each page</li>
<li>Ensure your sitemap is updated</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>3. Weak or Thin Content</h2>

<p>
Google ranks websites with  
<strong>high-quality, helpful, and keyword-optimized content</strong>.
</p>

<p>
If your content is:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Too short</li>
<li>Not helpful</li>
<li>Not targeting search intent</li>
</ul>

<p>
👉 It won’t rank.
</p>

<p>
👉 Fix: Publish content targeting  
<strong>long-tail SEO keywords for small businesses in Kenya</strong>.
</p>

---

<h2>4. No Internal Linking Structure</h2>

<p>
Your website must guide both users and Google.
</p>

<p>
Without internal linking:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Google struggles to crawl your site</li>
<li>Users don’t navigate properly</li>
</ul>

<p>
👉 Fix:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Link to <a href="#services" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">SEO services</a></li>
<li>Link to <a href="#portfolio" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">case studies</a></li>
<li>Link to <a href="#contact" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">contact section</a></li>
</ul>

---

<h2>5. Poor Technical SEO</h2>

<p>
Technical issues can block your rankings completely.
</p>

<p>
Common problems:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Slow website speed</li>
<li>Mobile issues</li>
<li>Broken links</li>
<li>No HTTPS</li>
</ul>

<p>
👉 Learn more here:  
<a href="/blog/technical-seo-explained-2026.html" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">
Technical SEO explained simply
</a>
</p>

---

<h2>6. No Backlinks (Authority Problem)</h2>

<p>
Google trusts websites that other websites link to.
</p>

<p>
If you have:
</p>

<ul>
<li>No backlinks</li>
<li>No online presence</li>
</ul>

<p>
👉 Your rankings will stay low.
</p>

---

<h2>7. Targeting Highly Competitive Keywords</h2>

<p>
Trying to rank for broad keywords is difficult.
</p>

<p>
Instead of:
</p>
<ul>
<li>“SEO”</li>
</ul>

<p>
Target:
</p>

<ul>
<li>“affordable SEO services for small businesses in Nairobi”</li>
<li>“local SEO expert for shops in Kenya”</li>
</ul>

